	irico group new energy compa
	
IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited Appoints Ni Huadong as Secretary to the Board
May 8 17
The board of directors of IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited announced that Mr. Ni Huadong was appointed as the secretary to the board of the company. Ni Huadong is a member of the Chinese Communist Party and holds a bachelor's degree. Mr. Ni started work in August 1998 and had served successively as investment specialist of the securities department, head of the corporate management center, assistant to the head and deputy head of the securities department of Nanjing Hua Dong Electronics Group Limited; deputy director of the secretariat of the board of directors and representative of securities affairs of Nanjing Huadong Electronics Information & Technology Co. Ltd.; deputy general manager of Nanjing Tian Xi Investment Co., Ltd; general manager of Hong Kong Hua Jin Chen Technology Company Limited; and representative of securities affairs, head of the securities department and head of office of the board of directors of Huadong Technology. Mr. Ni obtained the Qualification Certificate of Secretary to the Board of Directors issued by Shenzhen Stock Exchange in December 2010 and is experienced in securities management, capital operation and investor relations management.


IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 30, 2017
Apr 24 17
IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited, Annual General Meeting, Jun 30, 2017, at 09:00 China Standard Time. Location: No. 1 Caihong Road Xianyang Shaanxi Province China Agenda: To consider and approve the report of the board of directors of the company for the financial year ended 31 December 2016; to consider and approve the report of the supervisory committee of the company for year 2016; to consider and approve the audited financial statements of the company for year 2016; to consider and approve the profit distribution proposal of the company for Year 2016; to consider and authorize the board to determine the interim profit distribution for the year ending 31 December 2017; to consider and approve the appointment of the PRC auditor and international auditor of the company, respectively, for year 2017 and authorize the board to determine their remunerations; to consider and approve the authorization to the board to determine the annual remuneration of the directors and the supervisors of the company for year 2017; and to consider and approve the resolution in relation to the grant of an unconditional general mandate to the Board to issue shares.


IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited Reports Consolidated Cash Flow Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Apr 18 17
IRICO Group New Energy Company Limited reported consolidated cash flow results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported net cash from operating activities was RMB 100,277,000 against RMB 108,692,000 a year ago. Purchases of property, plant and equipment was RMB 199,163,000 against RMB 383,200,000 a year ago.








 












